  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 561612 federal contract obligations total $5.4B in FY2026 to date, with 4,764 awards and an average award size of $1.1M. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Obligations are down 9.4% year over year. Fiscal-year history shows obligations of $5B in FY21, $5.1B in FY22, $5.6B in FY23, $5.6B in FY24, and $6B in FY25 before the current $5.4B level. The Department of Homeland Security accounts for the largest share of buying at $3.1B, followed by the Department of State at $760M and the Department of Justice at $750M. At the vendor level, METROPOLITAN SECURITY SERVICES, INC. leads with $530M in obligations, followed by AMENTUM SERVICES, INC. at $504M and THE GEO GROUP, INC. at $398M. This profile shows concentration in a few large buyers and vendors and a recent pullback from the FY25 peak to the current FY2026 to date total.",
